The #MyODLRAlibi challenge has returned for the holidays! Oscar de la Renta, house-friend @tinaleung and our socially-distant studio audience invite you to design your very own Alibi bag with a seasonal twist. 

Doodle, adorn, and/or make a 3-D masterpiece and share your interpretation with us. The creator, hand-selected by Co-Creative Directors Fernando Garcia and Laura Kim, will win an Oscar de la Renta Alibi bag. ⁣
⁣
How to Participate: ⁣
⁣
Download the folding pattern from the link in our bio, print it, add your creative touch and assemble!⁣
⁣
Upload an image or video on Instagram of your assembled bag with the hashtag #MyODLRAlibi and #odlrholiday to win.
⁣
This contest runs until Saturday, December 26th 10AM EST

Show us your Alibi. Oscar de la Renta and design team member, David Alperti (@princemonkey), invite you to design your very own Alibi bag. Inspired by vintage luggage, the house-favorite Alibi combines old-world and contemporary appeal. ⁣
⁣
Doodle, adorn, and/or make a 3-D masterpiece and share your interpretation with us. The top three creators, hand-selected by co-creative directors Fernando Garcia and Laura Kim, will win an Oscar de la Renta Alibi. ⁣
⁣
How to Participate: ⁣
⁣
Download the folding pattern from the link in our bio, print it, add your creative touch and assemble!⁣
⁣
Upload an image or digital file on Instagram of your assembled bag with the hashtag #MyODLRAlibi to win.
⁣
This contest runs until Friday, May 22nd 10 AM EST

If you missed the conversation yesterday, co-creative director @fernandogarciam1205 and @mollyddickson went live for a discussion about the creative process behind Scarlett Johansson’s Oscars and Vanity Fair Oscar Party gowns. From initial fitting to carpet, they give a detailed visual account of how the moment came to life. Watch here. ⁣
⁣
Plus, just for you, Molly has styled ready-to-wear looks based on the red carpet moments. Head to the link in our bio to discover her selects. ⁣

node.title: Tune In: The Process Behind Scarlett Johansson's Oscars Gowns

Discover the making of @billieeilish’s #metgala gown. Co-Creative Directors @fernandogarciam1205 and @tokibunbun bring the Met Gala co-chair’s Old Hollywood vision to life with a corseted blush tulle gown, inspired by Marilyn Monroe. @voguemagazine follows from ideation to our New York City atelier, to the day of the Gala. Thank you @billieeilish, @voguemagazine and @denagia. It was truly a one-of-a-kind moment. #odlrredcarpet 

Visit the link in bio to discover the entire journey.

node.text:
A closer look at @anokyai’s dress of dreams, which was hand-embroidered in our atelier leading up to the #metgala. Emblazoned with light-catching crystals, the celestial motif dazzles on the carpet. #odlrredcarpet 

Styled by @mr_carlos_nazario

Come behind the scenes in our atelier for an exclusive glimpse at the creation of @kaiagerber's #metgala looks. Inspired by Bianca Jagger, her faille Met Gala carpet gown features hand-placed ivy embroideries, which line the bust. For the after-parties, Kaia made a daring statement in a black rendition of a #odlrprespring2022 floral beaded cocktail dress, which accounts for over 80 hours of handwork in our atelier. #odlrredcarpet

Styled by @andrewmukamal
Video edited by @maxwellswift
